documents.title: Company Policies & Guidelines
documents.content:
# Company Policies & Guidelines

## Remote Work Policy

### Eligibility
All full-time employees who have completed their probation period (90 days) are eligible for remote work arrangements. Remote work is a privilege, not a right, and may be modified based on business needs.

### Working Hours
- Core hours are 10:00 AM to 4:00 PM in your local timezone
- You must be available for meetings and collaboration during core hours
- Flexible hours outside of core hours are permitted with manager approval

### Equipment & Setup
- The company provides a laptop and monitor for all remote workers
- A $500 home office stipend is available annually for ergonomic equipment
- Reliable internet connection (minimum 50 Mbps) is required
- VPN must be used for all company network access

### Communication Expectations
- Respond to Slack messages within 2 hours during work hours
- Keep your calendar updated with availability
- Enable video for all team meetings unless bandwidth issues occur
- Weekly 1:1 meetings with your manager are mandatory

## Paid Time Off (PTO) Policy

### Annual Allocation
- 0-2 years of service: 15 days PTO
- 2-5 years of service: 20 days PTO
- 5+ years of service: 25 days PTO

### Requesting Time Off
- Submit PTO requests at least 2 weeks in advance
- Emergency time off should be communicated to your manager immediately
- PTO must be approved by your direct manager
- Unused PTO does not carry over to the next year (use it or lose it)

### Holidays
The company observes 10 paid holidays per year:
- New Year's Day
- Martin Luther King Jr. Day
- Presidents' Day
- Memorial Day
- Independence Day
- Labor Day
- Thanksgiving (2 days)
- Christmas Eve
- Christmas Day

## Expense Reimbursement

### Eligible Expenses
- Business travel (flights, hotels, transportation)
- Client entertainment (with prior approval)
- Professional development and training
- Home office equipment (within annual budget)

### Submission Process
1. Submit expenses through ExpenseBot within 30 days of incurrence
2. Include itemized receipts for all expenses over $25
3. Categorize expenses correctly
4. Manager approval required for expenses over $500
5. Reimbursement processed within 10 business days

## Code of Conduct

### Professional Behavior
- Treat all colleagues with respect and dignity
- Maintain confidentiality of company and client information
- Report conflicts of interest immediately
- Dress appropriately for video calls and in-person meetings

### Anti-Harassment Policy
We have zero tolerance for harassment of any kind. Report any incidents to HR immediately through our confidential reporting system.

documents.title: TechFlow Product FAQ
documents.content:
# Product FAQ - TechFlow Platform

## General Questions

### What is TechFlow?
TechFlow is an all-in-one project management and collaboration platform designed for modern software teams. It combines task management, code repository integration, CI/CD pipelines, and team communication into a single unified experience.

### What platforms is TechFlow available on?
TechFlow is available as:
- Web application (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)
- Desktop apps for Windows and macOS
- Mobile apps for iOS and Android
- API for custom integrations

### What is the pricing structure?
- **Free Tier**: Up to 5 users, 3 projects, basic features
- **Team Plan**: $12/user/month, unlimited projects, advanced analytics
- **Enterprise Plan**: Custom pricing, SSO, dedicated support, SLA guarantees

## Features & Functionality

### How do I create a new project?
1. Click the "+" button in the sidebar
2. Select "New Project"
3. Choose a template (Kanban, Scrum, or Custom)
4. Add team members and set permissions
5. Configure integrations (GitHub, Jira, Slack)

### Can I integrate TechFlow with GitHub?
Yes! TechFlow offers native GitHub integration. To set it up:
1. Go to Project Settings â†’ Integrations
2. Click "Connect GitHub"
3. Authorize the TechFlow GitHub App
4. Select repositories to sync
5. Enable automatic issue sync and PR tracking

### How does the AI assistant work?
Our AI assistant, TechFlow AI, can:
- Summarize meeting notes automatically
- Generate task descriptions from requirements
- Suggest task assignments based on team capacity
- Predict project completion dates
- Answer questions about your project data

### What are Workflows?
Workflows are customizable automation rules. Examples:
- Automatically assign QA review when a task moves to "Testing"
- Send Slack notifications when blockers are identified
- Create follow-up tasks when bugs are marked as "Resolved"

## Troubleshooting

### Why are my notifications not working?
Check these common issues:
1. Browser notification permissions are enabled
2. Email notifications are enabled in Settings â†’ Notifications
3. Your email is not in spam folder
4. Push notifications are enabled on mobile

### The app is running slowly. What can I do?
Try these solutions:
1. Clear browser cache and cookies
2. Disable browser extensions temporarily
3. Check your internet connection speed
4. Reduce the number of open projects/tabs
5. Contact support if issues persist

### I can't access a project. What should I do?
This usually means:
- You haven't been added to the project team
- Your account permissions have changed
- The project has been archived
Contact your project admin or workspace owner to resolve access issues.

## Security & Privacy

### Is my data encrypted?
Yes, all data is encrypted:
- At rest: AES-256 encryption
- In transit: TLS 1.3
- Backups: Encrypted and stored in geographically distributed locations

### Where is my data stored?
Data is stored in AWS data centers. Enterprise customers can choose their data region:
- US (Virginia)
- EU (Frankfurt)
- APAC (Singapore)

### Does TechFlow comply with GDPR?
Yes, TechFlow is fully GDPR compliant. We provide:
- Data export functionality
- Right to deletion (account removal)
- Transparent privacy policy
- Data Processing Agreement available on request

documents.title: TechFlow API Documentation
documents.content:
# TechFlow API Documentation

## Overview

The TechFlow API is a RESTful API that allows you to programmatically interact with your TechFlow data. All API endpoints are available at `https://api.techflow.io/v1/`.

## Authentication

### API Keys
Generate API keys in Settings â†’ API â†’ Generate New Key. Include your API key in all requests:

```
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY
```

### Rate Limits
- Free tier: 100 requests/minute
- Team plan: 1,000 requests/minute
- Enterprise: 10,000 requests/minute

Rate limit headers are included in all responses:
- `X-RateLimit-Limit`: Max requests per minute
- `X-RateLimit-Remaining`: Remaining requests
- `X-RateLimit-Reset`: Unix timestamp when limit resets

## Core Endpoints

### Projects

#### List Projects
```
GET /projects
```

Query Parameters:
- `page` (int): Page number, default 1
- `limit` (int): Items per page, max 100, default 20
- `status` (string): Filter by status (active, archived)

Response:
```json
{
  "data": [
    {
      "id": "proj_abc123",
      "name": "My Project",
      "description": "Project description",
      "created_at": "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z",
      "status": "active"
    }
  ],
  "pagination": {
    "page": 1,
    "limit": 20,
    "total": 45
  }
}
```

#### Create Project
```
POST /projects
```

Request Body:
```json
{
  "name": "New Project",
  "description": "Description here",
  "template": "kanban",
  "team_members": ["user_123", "user_456"]
}
```

### Tasks

#### List Tasks
```
GET /projects/:project_id/tasks
```

Query Parameters:
- `status`: Filter by status (todo, in_progress, review, done)
- `assignee`: Filter by user ID
- `priority`: Filter by priority (low, medium, high, urgent)
- `due_before`: Filter tasks due before date (ISO 8601)

#### Create Task
```
POST /projects/:project_id/tasks
```

Request Body:
```json
{
  "title": "Implement feature X",
  "description": "Full description with markdown support",
  "assignee_id": "user_123",
  "priority": "high",
  "due_date": "2024-02-01T00:00:00Z",
  "labels": ["feature", "backend"]
}
```

#### Update Task
```
PATCH /tasks/:task_id
```

All fields are optional. Only include fields you want to update.

### Webhooks

#### Configure Webhooks
```
POST /webhooks
```

Request Body:
```json
{
  "url": "https://your-server.com/webhook",
  "events": ["task.created", "task.updated", "project.archived"],
  "secret": "your_webhook_secret"
}
```

Supported Events:
- `task.created`, `task.updated`, `task.deleted`
- `project.created`, `project.archived`
- `comment.created`
- `member.added`, `member.removed`

## Error Handling

All errors return a JSON object with:
```json
{
  "error": {
    "code": "invalid_request",
    "message": "Human-readable error message",
    "details": {}
  }
}
```

Common Error Codes:
- `400 Bad Request`: Invalid request body or parameters
- `401 Unauthorized`: Missing or invalid API key
- `403 Forbidden`: Insufficient permissions
- `404 Not Found`: Resource doesn't exist
- `429 Too Many Requests`: Rate limit exceeded
- `500 Internal Server Error`: Server-side error

## SDKs

Official SDKs available:
- JavaScript/TypeScript: `npm install @techflow/sdk`
- Python: `pip install techflow-sdk`
- Go: `go get github.com/techflow/go-sdk`
- Ruby: `gem install techflow`

Example (JavaScript):
```javascript
import { TechFlow } from '@techflow/sdk';

const client = new TechFlow({ apiKey: 'YOUR_API_KEY' });

const projects = await client.projects.list();
const task = await client.tasks.create('proj_123', {
  title: 'New Task',
  priority: 'high'
});
```

documents.title: New Employee Onboarding Guide
documents.content:
# New Employee Onboarding Guide

## Welcome to TechFlow!

Congratulations on joining our team! This guide will help you get started during your first weeks at TechFlow.

## Your First Day

### Morning Checklist
1. Check in with HR to complete paperwork
2. Collect your laptop and equipment from IT
3. Meet your manager for orientation
4. Get your badge and building access
5. Set up your desk and workstation

### Account Setup
You'll receive emails with setup instructions for:
- Company email (Gmail)
- Slack workspace
- TechFlow platform (of course!)
- GitHub organization access
- 1Password team vault
- Zoom account

All passwords should be stored in 1Password. Never share passwords via email or Slack.

## Your First Week

### Day 1-2: Orientation
- Company overview presentation with the People team
- Product demo and platform walkthrough
- Meet your team members
- Review team goals and current projects

### Day 3-4: Technical Setup
- Development environment setup (follow the Dev Setup Guide)
- Code review process training
- CI/CD pipeline overview
- Access to development, staging, and production environments

### Day 5: Team Integration
- Shadow a team member
- Attend team standup
- Review your 30-60-90 day plan with your manager
- Start your first onboarding task

## Key Resources

### Documentation
- **Confluence**: Company wiki and documentation
- **Notion**: Team-specific notes and meeting records
- **GitHub Wiki**: Technical documentation and architecture docs

### Communication
- **Slack**: Primary communication tool
  - #general: Company-wide announcements
  - #engineering: Technical discussions
  - #random: Fun and casual conversations
  - Your team channel will be shared by your manager
- **Email**: For external communication and formal requests

### Meetings
- **Daily Standup**: 9:30 AM, 15 minutes
- **Weekly Team Sync**: Wednesdays at 2 PM
- **Sprint Planning**: Every other Monday
- **All Hands**: Monthly, first Friday

## Support & Questions

### Who to Contact
- **IT Issues**: #it-help on Slack or it@techflow.io
- **HR Questions**: hr@techflow.io or book time with People team
- **Technical Questions**: Your tech lead or #engineering-help
- **Expense/Finance**: finance@techflow.io

### Your Onboarding Buddy
You'll be assigned an onboarding buddy who:
- Will check in with you daily during your first week
- Can answer questions about company culture
- Will help you navigate internal tools and processes
- Is available for coffee chats and casual questions

## 30-60-90 Day Expectations

### First 30 Days
- Complete all onboarding training
- Understand team processes and workflows
- Ship your first small contribution
- Build relationships with immediate team members

### Days 31-60
- Take ownership of a small feature or project
- Participate actively in code reviews
- Contribute to technical discussions
- Identify areas for improvement

### Days 61-90
- Lead a small project or initiative
- Mentor newer team members
- Demonstrate independence in daily work
- Complete probation review with manager

## Company Culture

### Our Values
1. **Customer Obsession**: Every decision starts with the customer
2. **Bias for Action**: Move fast, learn faster
3. **Radical Transparency**: Share information openly
4. **Continuous Improvement**: Always be learning

### Social Events
- Monthly team happy hours
- Quarterly all-hands celebrations
- Annual company retreat
- Interest-based clubs (running, gaming, book club)

Welcome aboard! We're excited to have you on the team. ðŸš€

documents.title: Security Guidelines & Best Practices
documents.content:
# Security Guidelines & Best Practices

## Overview

Security is everyone's responsibility at TechFlow. This guide outlines our security policies and best practices that all employees must follow.

## Password & Authentication

### Password Requirements
- Minimum 16 characters
- Mix of uppercase, lowercase, numbers, and symbols
- Never reuse passwords across services
- Use 1Password for all password management
- Change passwords immediately if compromise is suspected

### Two-Factor Authentication (2FA)
2FA is mandatory for all company accounts:
- Use hardware security keys (YubiKey) when possible
- Google Authenticator or 1Password TOTP as backup
- SMS-based 2FA is NOT allowed for sensitive systems
- Report lost 2FA devices immediately to IT

### Single Sign-On (SSO)
- Use SSO for all supported applications
- Never bypass SSO by creating direct accounts
- Report any SSO failures to IT immediately

## Data Classification

### Confidential Data
Examples: Customer PII, financial records, source code, API keys
- Never share externally without legal approval
- Encrypt before storing or transmitting
- Access on need-to-know basis only
- Delete when no longer needed

### Internal Data
Examples: Internal documentation, meeting notes, team communications
- Share only within the company
- Use approved tools (Slack, Notion, Confluence)
- Be cautious when screen sharing

### Public Data
Examples: Marketing materials, public blog posts, open-source code
- Approved for external sharing
- Still follow brand guidelines

## Secure Development Practices

### Code Security
- Never commit secrets, API keys, or credentials to repositories
- Use environment variables or secrets managers
- Run security scanners before merging code
- Follow OWASP Top 10 guidelines
- Keep dependencies updated

### Code Review Security Checklist
- [ ] No hardcoded credentials
- [ ] Input validation implemented
- [ ] SQL injection prevention verified
- [ ] XSS prevention measures in place
- [ ] Authentication and authorization checked
- [ ] Sensitive data properly encrypted

### Secrets Management
- Use HashiCorp Vault for production secrets
- AWS Secrets Manager for cloud credentials
- 1Password for personal/team secrets
- Rotate secrets every 90 days
- Use different credentials per environment

## Device Security

### Laptop Security
- Enable full disk encryption (FileVault/BitLocker)
- Enable automatic screen lock (5 minutes)
- Keep OS and software updated
- Install only approved software
- Use VPN when on public networks
- Report lost or stolen devices immediately

### Mobile Devices
- Enable device passcode/biometrics
- Keep devices updated
- Enable remote wipe capability
- Don't jailbreak or root devices
- Only install apps from official stores

## Incident Response

### What to Report
- Phishing emails or suspicious messages
- Unauthorized access attempts
- Lost or stolen devices
- Accidental data exposure
- Suspicious activity on your accounts
- Security vulnerabilities discovered

### How to Report
1. **Immediate**: Message #security-incident on Slack
2. **Email**: security@techflow.io
3. **After hours**: Call the security hotline (in 1Password)

### Don't Do This
- Don't try to investigate incidents yourself
- Don't delete evidence (emails, logs)
- Don't share incident details broadly
- Don't wait to report (time is critical)

## Physical Security

### Office Access
- Badge in and out every time
- Don't tailgate or let others tailgate
- Challenge unfamiliar faces
- Lock your computer when leaving desk
- Secure sensitive documents in cabinets

### Visitor Policy
- All visitors must be registered in advance
- Visitors must be escorted at all times
- Visitors cannot access secure areas
- Report unescorted visitors immediately

## Phishing & Social Engineering

### Recognizing Phishing
- Urgent or threatening language
- Requests for credentials or personal info
- Suspicious sender addresses
- Links that don't match expected destinations
- Attachments from unknown senders

### What to Do
1. Don't click links or download attachments
2. Don't reply to the message
3. Forward to phishing@techflow.io
4. Delete the message
5. If you clicked, report immediately

## Compliance

### Training Requirements
- Complete security awareness training annually
- Role-specific training as assigned
- Acknowledge security policies on hire and annually

### Audits
- Cooperate fully with security audits
- Maintain accurate logs and records
- Report potential compliance issues

## Questions?

Contact the security team:
- Slack: #security or @security-team
- Email: security@techflow.io
- Weekly security office hours: Thursdays 2-3 PM

- `500 Internal Server Error`: Server-side error

## SDKs

Official SDKs available:
- JavaScript/TypeScript: `npm install @techflow/sdk`
- Python: `pip install techflow-sdk`
- Go: `go get github.com/techflow/go-sdk`
- Ruby: `gem install techflow`

Example (JavaScript):
```javascript
import { TechFlow } from '@techflow/sdk';

const client = new TechFlow({ apiKey: 'YOUR_API_KEY' });

const projects = await client.projects.list();
const task = await client.tasks.create('proj_123', {
  title: 'New Task',
  priority: 'high'
});
```

# Security Guidelines & Best Practices

## Overview

Security is everyone's responsibility at TechFlow. This guide outlines our security policies and best practices that all employees must follow.

## Password & Authentication

### Password Requirements
- Minimum 16 characters
- Mix of uppercase, lowercase, numbers, and symbols
- Never reuse passwords across services
- Use 1Password for all password management
- Change passwords immediately if compromise is suspected

### Two-Factor Authentication (2FA)
2FA is mandatory for all company accounts:
- Use hardware security keys (YubiKey) when possible
- Google Authenticator or 1Password TOTP as backup
- SMS-based 2FA is NOT allowed for sensitive systems
- Report lost 2FA devices immediately to IT

### Single Sign-On (SSO)
- Use SSO for all supported applications
- Never bypass SSO by creating direct accounts
- Report any SSO failures to IT immediately

## Data Classification

### Confidential Data
Examples: Customer PII, financial records, source code, API keys
- Never share externally without legal approval
- Encrypt before storing or transmitting
- Access on need-to-know basis only
- Delete when no longer needed

### Internal Data
Examples: Internal documentation, meeting notes, team communications
- Share only within the company
- Use approved tools (Slack, Notion, Confluence)
- Be cautious when screen sharing

### Public Data
Examples: Marketing materials, public blog posts, open-source code
- Approved for external sharing
- Still follow brand guidelines

## Secure Development Practices

### Code Security
- Never commit secrets, API keys, or credentials to repositories
- Use environment variables or secrets managers
- Run security scanners before merging code
- Follow OWASP Top 10 guidelines
- Keep dependencies updated

### Code Review Security Checklist
- [ ] No hardcoded credentials
- [ ] Input validation implemented
- [ ] SQL injection prevention verified
- [ ] XSS prevention measures in place
- [ ] Authentication and authorization checked
- [ ] Sensitive data properly encrypted

### Secrets Management
- Use HashiCorp Vault for production secrets
- AWS Secrets Manager for cloud credentials
- 1Password for personal/team secrets
- Rotate secrets every 90 days
- Use different credentials per environment

## Device Security

### Laptop Security
- Enable full disk encryption (FileVault/BitLocker)
- Enable automatic screen lock (5 minutes)
- Keep OS and software updated
- Install only approved software
- Use VPN when on public networks
- Report lost or stolen devices immediately

### Mobile Devices
- Enable device passcode/biometrics
- Keep devices updated
- Enable remote wipe capability
- Don't jailbreak or root devices
- Only install apps from official stores

## Incident Response

### What to Report
- Phishing emails or suspicious messages
- Unauthorized access attempts
- Lost or stolen devices
- Accidental data exposure
- Suspicious activity on your accounts
- Security vulnerabilities discovered

### How to Report
1. **Immediate**: Message #security-incident on Slack
2. **Email**: security@techflow.io
3. **After hours**: Call the security hotline (in 1Password)

### Don't Do This
- Don't try to investigate incidents yourself
- Don't delete evidence (emails, logs)
- Don't share incident details broadly
- Don't wait to report (time is critical)

## Physical Security

### Office Access
- Badge in and out every time
- Don't tailgate or let others tailgate
- Challenge unfamiliar faces
- Lock your computer when leaving desk
- Secure sensitive documents in cabinets

### Visitor Policy
- All visitors must be registered in advance
- Visitors must be escorted at all times
- Visitors cannot access secure areas
- Report unescorted visitors immediately

## Phishing & Social Engineering

- All visitors must be registered in advance

## Phishing & Social Engineering

### Recognizing Phishing
- Urgent or threatening language
- Requests for credentials or personal info
- Suspicious sender addresses
- Links that don't match expected destinations
- Attachments from unknown senders

### What to Do
1. Don't click links or download attachments
2. Don't reply to the message
3. Forward to phishing@techflow.io
4. Delete the message
5. If you clicked, report immediately
